headline: Cigna’s Reassurances About PBM Business Lift Stock
summary: Cigna Group’s shares are up about 3% in trading Thursday, showing that investors don’t think the recent round of changes out of Washington will fundamentally alter the company’s outlook.  Cigna is the parent of one of the largest pharmacy-benefit managers.  On Wednesday, the Federal Trade Commission announced a settlement with the company.

headline: Cigna’s (NYSE:CI) Q4 CY2025 Sales Beat Estimates
summary: Health insurance company Cigna (NYSE:CI) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 10.3% year on year to $72.47 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $280 billion at the midpoint came in 0.9% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $8.08 per share was 2.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
